Class FlexibleObjectWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • freemarker.ext.beans.BeansWrapper
      • freemarker.template.DefaultObjectWrapper
        • org.microbean.freemarker.FlexibleObjectWrapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ObjectWrapper, ObjectWrapperAndUnwrapper, ObjectWrapperWithAPISupport, RichObjectWrapper, WriteProtectable

    public class FlexibleObjectWrapper
extends DefaultObjectWrapper
    A DefaultObjectWrapper that uses a Map of ModelFactory instances indexed by Class instances to assist in wrapping Objects.
    Author:
    Laird Nelson

    • Method Detail

      • getModelFactory

        protected ModelFactory getModelFactory(Class c)
        Returns a ModelFactory suitable for the supplied Class.

        This method never returns null.

        Overrides of this method must never return null.

        This implementation tries to return a ModelFactory as found in the Map of such ModelFactory instances provided at construction time. If there is no such ModelFactory, then the return value of invoking the super.getModelFactory(Class) is returned instead.

        Overrides:
        getModelFactory in class BeansWrapper
        Parameters:
        c - the Class for which a ModelFactory is desired; must not be null
        Returns:
        a ModelFactory; never null
        See Also:
        BeansWrapper.getModelFactory(Class)
